e superior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 8:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3126.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Sorry for the noob question, MA vs MT.</span><hr size=1> I recently returned to EQ after a break and leaving my guild.  I have joined a much smaller guild where I am the second highest tank in terms of lvls, equip, hps, etc.  In my old guild I rarely got to tank and only assisted the MT on raids normally.  Got to tank ST some and a few other places but not much.  Usually only when the better equiped warriors went down.<br>
<br>
Anyway, we were killing Phinny and the cleric there said I should be Main Assist.  I joked about being a suxors tank and he said &quot;I said Main Assist not Main Tank&quot;.  Now in my warrior like brain I always assisted the Main Tank on our raids so I thought MA=MT.  I am guessing they do not have to be.<br>
<br>
Can someone explain in simple terms the difference?  Thank you in advance.<br>
<br>
Is this where another person who is not MT chooses the next target for MT and everyone to assist for target selection?  I did this in the PON Hedge Event to keep an aggro'd mob so quest NPC didn't wander off.  I would break off mob at 50% and start taunting a mez'd mob.  When I saw enrage message from mob everyone was killing I broke mez and started attacking.  MT then came after first mob was dead and I let aggro transfer to him.<br>
<br>
Friedrick embarrassed to be 63 Warlord and not know the difference <p>&lt;a target=&quot;new&quot; href=&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=365390&quot;&gt;Friedrick's Magelo Profile&lt;/a&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=varaho1>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1482<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 8:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3126.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sorry for the noob question, MA vs MT.</span><hr size=1> MA: Main Assist, the person that tells everyone else what to kill. <br>
<br>
MT: Main Tank, the person who you try and get a mob to hit<br>
<br>
ST: Secondary Tank: backup for MT if stuff happens.<br>
<br>
SA: Secondary Assist: Backup for MA if MA goes down or MA misses something.<br>
<br>
OT: Off Tank, person who is tanking a mob that the raid force is not trying to kill at the moment.<br>
<br>
MA is not the same as MT its just that some people do both jobs at the same time.  <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Times New roman;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170513">Varaho Carnicero</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
60th Human Warlord Xegony Server</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:Times New roman;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>  &quot;This is my blade.<br>
It is my life.<br>
It is your death.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 289<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 12:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3126.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sorry for the noob question, MA vs MT.</span><hr size=1> The only real difference between MT and MA is that MT doesn't have to know what mobs are more dangerous or what mobs are mezzable, but the MA does (otherwise you're not doing your job).  Usually one person can do both jobs at the same time.<br>
<br>
I think every warrior that plans to be useful really should figure out at least the mezzable part and it's not very hard to figure out what's more dangerous based on empirical observation. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dwelfnvhal>DwelfnVhal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 1:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3126.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sorry for the noob question, MA vs MT.</span><hr size=1> There are occasions where in an encounter the MT will be tanking solo with a CH chain whilst the MA directs the rest of the raid force to kill adds or other mobs before returning to main target - making the distinction between the Main Tank and the Main Assist just gives that little bit more flexibility... <br>
<br>
Val <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abividad>Abividad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 2:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3126.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sorry for the noob question, MA vs MT.</span><hr size=1> My small guild is just starting to do raids that need better co-ordination with MT, MA and so on. I know there is a list of slowable mobs here <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.dith.demon.co.uk/slows/">www.dith.demon.co.uk/slows/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
