br>
<br>
As far as tanks, my guild uses the terms interchangably. We generally set a MA/SA/TA and they announce their targets when we're split tanking. Generally we split 2 mez 3+. Its the SA's responsibility to find the unmezzed mob raping the raidgroup and give it a hug <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Sage Roma Emeraldheart</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Level 65 Coercer<br>
The Arisen<br>
Terris-Thule<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84333">Look Under My Dress</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Freddrick Transient</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Level 65 Overlord<br>
Dead Sexy Froaker<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=620383">Take Off My Pants</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dakkin2>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/03 6:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3126.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sorry for the noob question, MA vs MT.</span><hr size=1> In many situations, such as when fighting somewhere you're likely to get a lot of mezzed mobs, it's a good idea to make the MA the same person as the MT so he can call assist when he's taunted and starting to whale away on the mob.<br>
<br>
When fighting anything that has a good chance of killing your MT (e.g. deathtouches), it's often a bad idea to make the MA and MT the same person, since it makes it impractical for people to use /assist to find the current target of the mob, or to return to targeting the mob quickly after they've just finished doing something else.<br>
<br>
Most people make MA and MT the same person but it's not always the best thing to do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showPrevMessage?topicID=3126.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showNextMessage?topicID=3126.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3126.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.emailToFriend?topicID=3126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.threadControl?topicID=3126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3126.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post>